Indicates whether the deficiency has been corrected, a plan of correction has been devised, or the deficiency has yet to be corrected

The inspection cycle of deficiency, where 1 is the most recent cycle. Standard inspection cycles are counted sequentially into the past, complaint inspection cycles are counted annually into the past. If a defiency is found on a co-occurring standard and complaint inspection, it is assigned to the standard cycle.  Please refer to the 5-star Technical Users Guide for further information.
Indicates that the deficiency was found on a standard inspection
Indicates that the deficiency was found on a complaint inspection
